2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuk-election-polls-point-to-drubbing-for-pm-rishi-sunak-5725098%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Donald%20Trump's%20Hush%20Money%20Trial%20Verdict%20Can%20Affect%202024%20Election%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EJurors%20hearing%20the%20first-ever%20criminal%20trial%20of%20a%20former%20U.S.%20president%20could%20render%20their%20verdict%20in%20Donald%20Trump's%20hush%20money%20case%20as%20soon%20as%20next%20week%2C%20with%20potentially%20big%20implications%20for%20the%202024%20White%20House%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%2034%20counts%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20to%20cover%20up%20a%20payment%20that%20bought%20the%20silence%20of%20porn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%20shortly%20before%20the%202016%20election.%20Daniels%20had%20threatened%20to%20go%20public%20with%20her%20account%20of%20an%20alleged%202006%20sexual%20encounter%20with%20Trump%2C%20a%20liaison%20he%20denies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20case%20is%20widely%20seen%20as%20the%20least%20consequential%20of%20the%20four%20criminal%20prosecutions%20Trump%20faces.%20But%20it%20has%20meant%20the%20Republican%20presidential%20candidate%20spent%20more%20time%20in%20court%20than%20campaigning%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20and%20brought%20outsized%20attention%20to%20the%20only%20case%20likely%20to%20go%20to%20trial%20before%20his%20Nov.%205%20election%20face-off%20with%20Democratic%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20how%20three%20potential%20outcomes%20from%20the%20jury%20room%20--%20a%20guilty%20verdict%2C%20an%20acquittal%20or%20a%20hung%20jury%20--%20could%20affect%20the%20presidential%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGUILTY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpinion%20polls%20show%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20could%20pose%20significant%20political%20danger%20for%20Trump%20in%20an%20election%20that%20will%20potentially%20be%20decided%20by%20just%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20votes%20in%20a%20handful%20of%20battleground%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20in%20four%20Republicans%20said%20they%20would%20not%20vote%20for%20Trump%20if%20he%20is%20found%20guilty%20in%20a%20criminal%20trial%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Reuters%2FIpsos%20poll%20of%20registered%20voters%20in%20April.%20In%20the%20same%20survey%2C%2060%25%20of%20independents%20said%20they%20would%20not%20vote%20for%20Trump%20if%20he%20is%20convicted%20of%20a%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepublican%20and%20Democratic%20consultants%20have%20mixed%20views%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20a%20guilty%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhit%20Ayres%2C%20a%20Republican%20pollster%2C%20doubts%20that%20as%20many%20as%20a%20fourth%20of%20Republicans%20would%20actually%20shun%20Trump%20if%20he's%20convicted.%20But%20Ayres%20said%20even%20if%20just%20a%20small%20number%20of%20more%20moderate%20Republicans%20and%20independents%20are%20turned%20off%20by%20a%20guilty%20verdict%2C%20it%20could%20help%20Biden%20in%20a%20close%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Ayres%20said%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20New%20York%20case%2C%20which%20was%20brought%20by%20a%20Democratic%20prosecutor%20and%20relies%20on%20untested%20legal%20strategies%2C%20will%20help%20Trump%20and%20fellow%20Republicans%20frame%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20as%20a%20political%20hit%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20were%20trying%20to%20design%20a%20court%20case%20that%20would%20be%20easy%20for%20Republicans%20to%20dismiss%20as%20a%20partisan%20witch%20hunt%2C%20I%20would%20design%20exactly%20the%20case%20that's%20being%20brought%20in%20New%20York%2C%26quot%3B%20Ayres%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepublican%20consultant%20Tricia%20McLaughlin%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20former%20Trump%20primary%20challenger%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy's%20campaign%2C%20said%20she%20thought%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20would%20have%20a%20psychological%20impact%20on%20Trump%20because%20he%20hates%20losing.%20It%20would%20also%20divert%20more%20financial%20resources%20to%20legal%20bills%20because%20he%20would%20be%20almost%20certain%20to%20appeal%20a%20guilty%20verdict%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBill%20Galston%2C%20an%20analyst%20and%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20think%20tank%20in%20Washington%2C%20said%20he%20didn't%20expect%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20would%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20presidential%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20this%20amounts%20to%20lying%20about%20sex.%20I%20think%20the%20view%20probably%20of%20the%20majority%20of%20Americans%20is%20that%20everybody%20lies%20about%20sex%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Galston%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20on%20Democratic%20presidential%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20served%20in%20the%20administration%20of%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20whose%201990s%20tenure%20in%20the%20White%20House%20was%20marked%20by%20sex%20scandals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENOT%20GUILTY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20from%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20agree%20on%20one%20thing%3A%20An%20acquittal%20would%20be%20a%20huge%20victory%20for%20Trump%2C%20especially%20because%20he%20has%20claimed%20the%20trial%20is%20a%20sham%20political%20persecution%20aimed%20at%20derailing%20his%20presidential%20bid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20campaign%20trail%2C%20the%20candidate%20could%20use%20a%20not-guilty%20verdict%20in%20New%20York%20to%20claim%20the%20other%20cases%20against%20him%20also%20have%20no%20legal%20merit%2C%20McLaughlin%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20faces%20federal%20and%20state%20charges%20in%20Washington%20and%20Georgia%20of%20trying%20to%20overturn%20his%202020%20loss%20to%20Biden%20and%20federal%20charges%20in%20Florida%20of%20mishandling%20classified%20documents%20after%20leaving%20the%20White%20House%20in%202021.%20He%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20in%20all%20three%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20great%20fodder%20for%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20McLaughlin%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20will%20say%2C%20'I%20won%20this%20sham%20trial%2C%20this%20witch%20hunt%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20that's%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%20with%20the%20other%20trials.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%2FIpsos%20has%20not%20polled%20on%20how%20an%20acquittal%20would%20affect%20voters'%20views%20of%20the%20presidential%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaren%20Finney%2C%20a%20Democratic%20consultant%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20Clinton%20White%20House%2C%20said%20for%20Trump's%20core%20supporters%20%26quot%3Ban%20acquittal%20will%20make%20them%20feel%20vindicated%20and%20validated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20said%20the%20lurid%20details%20that%20came%20out%20in%20trial%20testimony%20and%20the%20case's%20central%20allegation%20-%20that%20Trump%20arranged%20a%20hush%20money%20payment%20to%20a%20porn%20star%20-%20could%20still%20damage%20him%20even%20if%20jurors%20find%20him%20not%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20come%20out%20during%20the%20case%20could%20turn%20off%20these%20suburban%20women%20that%20Trump%20still%20has%20a%20problem%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Finney%20said%2C%20although%20she%20said%20he%20would%20play%20an%20acquittal%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20victory.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHUNG%20JURY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%2012%20jurors%20hearing%20Trump's%20case%20can't%20agree%20on%20an%20unanimous%20verdict%2C%20the%20result%20will%20be%20a%20hung%20jury%20and%20the%20judge%20will%20have%20to%20declare%20a%20mistrial%2C%20legal%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20will%20spin%20a%20mistrial%20as%20a%20victory%2C%20the%20political%20consultants%20and%20analysts%20said%2C%20but%20without%20the%20validation%20that%20an%20acquittal%20would%20give%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20has%20kept%20Trump%20in%20the%20news%2C%20something%20he%20likes%2C%20said%20John%20Feehery%2C%20a%20Republican%20consultant%20who%20has%20worked%20for%20con