cuments-heart-case-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20has%20been%20charged%20with%2034%20counts%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20this%20one%20felony.%20That's%20the%20entirety%20of%20his%20indictment.%20There's%20one%20count%20for%20each%20of%2034%20invoices%2C%20checks%2C%20and%20Trump%20Organization%20ledger%20entries%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20the%20records%20that%20Trump%20allegedly%20%26quot%3Bcaused%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20falsified%20throughout%202017%2C%20his%20first%20year%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20for%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20allege%20that%20each%20falsified%20invoice%2C%20check%2C%20and%20ledger%20entry%20counts%20as%20a%20felony%20because%20it%20concealed%20an%20underlying%20crime.%20(They%20say%20the%20underlying%20crime%20is%20a%20state%20election%20law%20violation%20%E2%80%94%20more%20about%20that%20in%20a%20bit.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20were%20they%20allegedly%20falsified%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBragg%20says%20each%20of%20the%2034%20records%20disguised%20the%20true%20nature%20of%20a%20year's%20worth%20of%20payments%20to%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichael-cohen-trump-acquittal-better-financially-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMichael%2520Cohen%2520testified%2520that%2520he%2Che%2520might%2520run%2520for%2520Congress.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bfixer%26quot%3B-turned-foe%20Michael%20Cohen%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20making%20the%20payments%20look%20like%20monthly%20legal%20retainer%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20Bragg%20alleges%2C%20Trump%20wasn't%20paying%20Cohen%20a%20monthly%20retainer%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20instead%20concealing%20an%20illegal%20conspiracy%20to%20influence%20the%202016%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20compensating%20Cohen%20for%20legal%20work%20%E2%80%94%20Cohen%20testified%20he%20only%20did%20a%20few%20hours%20of%20work%20for%20Trump%20in%20all%20of%202017%20%E2%80%94%20the%20payments%20secretly%20reimbursed%20Cohen%20in%20monthly%20installments%20for%20a%20campaign-law-violating%20%24130%2C000%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstormy-daniels-donald-trump-witness-stand-hush-money-trial-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eporn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20prosecutors%20allege.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22michael%20cohen%20donald%20trump%20stormy%20daniels%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c12d1d23224ed04366075c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%2C%20flanked%20by%20his%20former%20lawyer%2C%20Michael%20Cohen%2C%20and%20Stormy%20Daniels.%3Cp%3EGetty%2FAP%2FSNL%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211b0abf8-9800-4f15-ac78-53bf5ee11458%5C%22%3EHow%20do%20they%20decide%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOK%20it's%20a%20little%20tricky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20business%20records%20were%20indeed%20falsified%20to%20hide%20hush%20money.%20That's%20the%20coverup%20of%20a%20coverup.%20And%20let's%20say%20that%20the%20hush-money%20payment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20silenced%20Daniels%20just%2011%20days%20before%20the%202016%20election%20%E2%80%94%20was%20itself%20illegal.%20That's%20a%20crime%20within%20a%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20not%20%3Cem%3Eterribly%3C%2Fem%3E%20tricky%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20faces%2034%20counts%20of%20only%20a%20single%20charge%2C%20first-degree%20falsifying%2C%20for%20which%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24679490-ny-v-trump-standard-jury-charge-falsifying-business-records-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estandard%20charging%20language%3C%2Fa%3E%20barely%20fills%20two%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20each%20count%2C%20the%20jury%20must%20consider%20just%20two%20things%3A%20whether%20Trump%20caused%20the%20record%20to%20be%20falsified%2C%20and%20whether%20he%20did%20so%20to%20hide%20his%20intent%20to%20commit%20%26quot%3Banother%20crime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20prosecutors%20meet%20their%20burden%20to%20prove%20both%20tiers%20%E2%80%94%20falsification%20and%20intent%20to%20conceal%20another%20crime%20%E2%80%94%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt%2C%20then%20Trump%20is%20guilty.%20If%20they%20don't%2C%20then%20Trump%20is%20not%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20prove%20that%20%26quot%3Banother%20crime%26quot%3B%20was%20actually%20committed.%20They%20just%20have%20to%20prove%20that%20Trump%20intended%20to%20commit%20another%20crime%20and%20then%20falsified%20records%20to%20hide%20his%20tracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20charge%20for%20this%20single%20felony%20should%20be%20easy%2C%20right%3F%20Clear-cut%20and%20beyond%20dispute%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20first-degree%20falsifying%20is%20the%20only%20law%20in%20Trump's%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20law%20jurors%20must%20understand%20and%20weigh%20when%20they%20begin%20deliberations%20as%20early%20as%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20allege%20that%20Trump%20falsified%20the%20hush-money%20reimbursements%20in%20order%20to%20conceal%20his%20intent%20to%20commit%20an%20obscure%20New%20York%20election-conspiracy%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20they%20mean%20by%20Trump's%20%26quot%3Bintent%20to%20commit%20another%20crime.%26quot%3B%20Under%20the%20prosecution%20theory%2C%20this%20%26quot%3Banother%20crime%26quot%3B%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hush-money-case-relies-never-used-election-conspiracy-law-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelection%20law%20section%2017-152%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20it%20makes%20it%20a%20misdemeanor%20to%20conspire%20to%20influence%20an%20election%20%26quot%3Bby%20unlawful%20means.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Section%2017-152%20of%20the%20New%20York%20state%20election%20law.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662c4ec523b29110d303df20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221438%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EManhattan%20prosecutors%20say%20violating%20this%20state%20election%20law%20makes%20Donald%20Trump%20a%20felon.%3Cp%3ENY%20State%20Election%20Law%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b1bcaff-9b45-454a-9a2f-bd8330e8e51e%5C%22%3EA%20crime%20within%20a%20crime%20within%20a%20crime%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20you%20see%2C%20to%20win%20a%20conviction%2C%20prosecutors%20must%20demonstrate%20three%20layers%20of%20unlawfulness%20involving%20at%20least%20three%20separate%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20alleging%20Trump%20committed%20a%20crime%20(under%20the%20Federal%20Elections%20Campaign%20Act)%20within%20a%20crime%20(under%20the%20state%20election-conspiracy%20law)%20within%20a%20crime%20(under%20the%20first-degree%20falsifying%20charge%20he's%20actually%20indicted%20on).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20Russian%20nesting%20doll%20of%20wrongdoing%2C%20though%20only%20the%20outermost%20doll%2C%20first-degree%20falsifying%2C%20needs%20to%20be%20proven%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20also%20plan%20to%20give%20jurors%20two%20alternatives%20to%20the%20FECA%20violation%2C%20that%20innermost%20of%20the%20three%20nesting%20dolls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20alternatives%20are%20a%20violation%20of%20federal%2C%20state%2C%20and%2For%20city%20tax%20laws%20(alleging%20that%20Cohen's%20hush-money%20reimbursements%20were%20unlawfully%20disguised%20as%20taxable%20income)%20and%20yet%20another%20records-falsification%20violation%20(alleging%20that%20Trump%20was%20responsible%20for%20bogus%20hush-money%20paperwork%20at%20the%20National%20Enquirer.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20three%20layers%20of%20wrongdoing%20under%20a%20half-dozen%20potentially%20applicable%20laws%2C%20all%20with%20their%20own%20wording%20and%20definitions%2C%20much%20of%20which%20had%20to%20be%20argued%20over%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bconspiracy%3F%26quot%3B%20What%20is%20%26quot%3Bintent%3F%26quot%3B%20What%20is%20%26quot%3Baccessorial%20liability%3F%26quot%3B%20Do%20those%20definitions%20differ%2C%20law%20to%20law%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%20were%20broader%2C%20more%20arcane%20questions%2C%20including%20this%20one%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMust%20jurors%20agree%20unanimously%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bunlawful%20means%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeaning%2C%20must%20all%2012%20jurors%20agree%20that%2C%20in%20causing%20Cohen%20to%20pay%20the%20hush%20money%2C%20Trump%20conspired%20to%20violate%20FECA%20campaign-contribution%20limits%3F%20Or%20can%20some%20jurors%20find%20that%20Trump%20conspired%20to%20violate%20tax%20law%2C%20while%20other%20jurors%20see%20the%20falsification%20of%20National%20Enquirer%20business%20records%20as%20the%20central%20offense%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20do%20jurors%20need%20to%20be%20unanimous%20in%20deciding%20which%20of%20the%20three%20options%2C%20if%20any%2C%20is%20the%20central%20unlawfulness%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20brings%20us%20back%20to%20Tuesday's%20charge%20conference%20and%20why%20the%20sides%20fought%20for%20three%20hours%20as%20the%20defendant%2C%20and%20many%20in%20the%20audience%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-nap-trial-affect-jury-legal-experts-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggled%20to%20stay%20awake%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%2C%20obviously%2C%20an%20extraordinarily%20important%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20defense%20lawyer%20Emil%20Bove%20told%20the%20judge%2C%20in%20arguing%20that%20jurors%20be%20instructed%20that%20they%20must%20unanimously%20decide%20on%20an%20underlying%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20critical%20point%20here%20is%20that%20the%20jury%20does%20not%20need%20to%20conclude%20unanimously%20what%20the%20specific%20unlawful%20means%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Colangelo%2C%20a%20prosecutor%2C%20argued%20back%20Tuesday%2C%20referring%20to%20%26quot%3Bwell-established%20New%20York%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20the%20key%20point%20here%20for%20this%20instruction%2C%26quot%3B%20Colangelo%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20to%20advise%20the%20jury%20that%2C%20yes%2C%20there%20has%20to%20be%20some%20unlawful%20means%2C%20and%20to%20alert%20them%20as%20to%20what%20those%20unlawful%20means%20are%2C%20but%20also%20advise%20them%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20unanimously%20agree%20on%20each%20of%20the%20unlawful%20means.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20your%20honor%20has%20some%20discretion%2C%26quot%3B%20countered%20Bove.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20was%20not%20swayed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20I%20understand%20what%20you're%20saying%2C%20what%20you%20mean%20when%20you're%20saying%20it's%20an%20important%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Merchan%20told%20Trump's%20lawyer.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you're%20asking%20me%20to%20do%20is%20change%20the%20law%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223394%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20a%20courtroom.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66266e3423b29110d3015779%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222263%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20appears%20in%20court%20for%20opening%20statements%20in%20his%20Manhattan%20hush-money%20trial.%3Cp%3EYuki%20Iwamura-Pool%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb55326f-400b-42e5-8cc2-2f84fac9f381%5C%22%3ECharging%20the%20jury%20is%20a%20tedious%20task%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20debate%20was%20granular%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20Bove%20pushed%20for%20longer%2C%20more%20complex%20definitions%20of%20such%20terms%20as%20%26quot%3Bcontribution%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bunlawful%20means.%26quot%3B%20This%20was%20in%20the%20apparent%20hope%20that%20the%20narrower%20the%20definitions%2C%20the%20less%20likely%20jurors%20would%20find%20that%20Trump's%20actions%20fell%20within%20their%20bounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20fought%20to%20keep%20the%20charge%20as%20simple%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20discussed%2C%20we%20think%20the%20jury%20needs%20less%2C%20not%20more%2C%20on%20FECA%20instructions%2C%26quot%3B%20Colangelo%2C%20the%20prosecutor%2C%20argued%20at%20one%20point%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20think%20the%20term%2C%20'for%20the%20purpose%20of%20influencing%20an%20election'%20is%20a%20pretty%20straightforward%20term%20that%20jurors%20can%20understand%2C%26quot%3B%20Colangelo%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20awarding%20the%20most%20%26quot%3Bwins%26quot%3B%20to%20prosecutors%2C%20Merchan%20chose%20brevity%20over%20expansiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20issues%20are%20confusing%20enough%2C%20I%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20it%20as%20easy%20as%20possible%20for%20the%20jury.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20told%20prosecutors%20and%20Trump's%20lawyers%20that%20he'll%20give%20them%20the%20final%20draft%20of%20his%20instructions%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20jurors%20to%20expect%20his%20charge%20to%20last%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%20an%20hour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flatest-trump-hush-money-battle-how-instruct-jurors-on-law-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716419841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664e280d20abc1efe8fc72d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flatest-trump-hush-money-battle-how-instruct-jurors-on-law-2024-