0goal%20by%20avoiding%20lifestyle%20creep%20and%20making%20choices%20like%20only%20buying%20used%20cars.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhenever%20we%20had%20extra%20money%2C%20we%20put%20that%20money%20toward%20our%20mortgage%20payment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20July%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20sent%20in%20our%20final%20mortgage%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAchieving%20this%20goal%2C%20which%20at%20one%20time%20seemed%20so%20far%20out%20of%20reach%2C%20became%20a%20reality%20in%20just%20under%2013%20years.%20I%20remember%20being%2023%20years%20old%20and%20looking%20in%20horror%20at%20a%20chart%20showing%20how%20much%20we'd%20pay%20the%20bank%20over%2030%20years%20for%20our%20%24170%2C000%20home%20in%20a%20suburb%20of%20Cleveland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here%20we%20are%2C%20ages%2039%20and%2037%2C%20mortgage-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20we%20decided%20it%20made%20sense%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20early%20mortgage%20payoff%20had%20been%20a%20major%20financial%20goal%20of%20ours%20since%202016.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20we%20were%20both%20feeling%20burned%20out%20between%20parenting%20our%20two%20young%20daughters%20and%20managing%20our%20careers.%20We%20weren't%20thrilled%20about%20the%20idea%20of%20working%20full%20time%20for%20another%2030%20years%20and%20potentially%20having%20little%20time%20left%20to%20enjoy%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20an%20editor%20for%20a%20publishing%20firm.%20My%20husband%20was%20a%20supervisor%20for%20a%20produce%20company%20in%20addition%20to%20working%20one%20weekend%20a%20month%20and%20several%20weeks%20a%20year%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Ohio%20National%20Guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20doing%20some%20research%20and%20calculations%2C%20we%20realized%20a%20combination%20of%20investing%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpaying-off-mortgage-early-pros-cons%5C%22%3Epaying%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20give%20us%20the%20more%20flexible%20lifestyle%20we%20had%20in%20mind.%20Ridding%20ourselves%20of%20our%20largest%20monthly%20bill%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20pursue%20a%20freelance%20writing%20career%2C%20and%20it%20would%20allow%20my%20husband%20to%20work%20many%20fewer%20hours.%20And%20that%20freedom%20could%20come%20much%20sooner%20than%20the%20standard%20timeline%20that%20dictates%20you%20make%20house%20payments%20for%2030%20years%20and%20work%20until%20you're%2066%20or%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20experts%20debate%20whether%20an%20early%20mortgage%20payoff%20is%20the%20right%20financial%20move%20for%20everyone%2C%20and%20there%20are%20some%20benefits%20to%20keeping%20a%20mortgage%20(such%20as%20having%20more%20money%20to%20invest%20while%20you're%20young)%2C%20we%20decided%20it%20was%20the%20right%20move%20for%20us.%20In%202016%2C%20we%20refinanced%20our%20%24110%2C000%20balance%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%20just%20over%203%25%2C%20and%20we%20zeroed%20in%20on%20paying%20it%20off%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20living%20within%20our%20means%20helped%20us%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReflecting%20on%20how%20we%20paid%20off%20the%20balance%20in%20less%20than%20four%20years%20with%20moderate%20incomes%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20most%20of%20the%20credit%20goes%20to%20simple%20financial%20lessons%20we%20learned%20from%20our%20parents.%20Chief%20among%20them%20is%20to%20live%20within%20your%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20things%2C%20this%20is%20a%20simple%20idea%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20always%20easy%20to%20execute.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flifestyle-creep%5C%22%3ELifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20real%20thing%2C%20and%20so%20is%20the%20pressure%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20Joneses.%20Our%20parents%20did%20not%20attend%20college%20and%20often%20raised%20their%20families%20on%20one%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20showed%20us%20that%20living%20within%20your%20means%20can%20be%20done%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20delay%20gratification%20and%20make%20careful%20choices%2C%20like%20cooking%20most%20of%20your%20meals%20at%20home%2C%20being%20content%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bstarter%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20always%20having%20designer%20clothes%20or%20the%20latest%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20buy%20used%20cars%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20my%20mom%20and%20dad%20always%20did%20was%20choose%20not%20to%20drive%20new%20vehicles%2C%20which%20experts%20say%20lose%2011%25%20of%20their%20value%20the%20minute%20you%20drive%20them%20off%20the%20lot%20anyway.%20We've%20followed%20suit.%20Sure%2C%20we%20could%20finance%20new%20cars%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20%24554%20per%20car%20a%20month%2C%20which%20is%20the%20average%20payment%20for%20a%20new%20vehicle%20in%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.experian.com%2Fblogs%2Fask-experian%2Fwhat-is-the-average-car-payment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20credit%20bureau%20Experian%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20we%20purchase%20low-mileage%20vehicles%20that%20are%20a%20few%20years%20old.%20We%20either%20pay%20for%20our%20cars%20in%20cash%20or%20buy%20them%20with%20low-interest%20auto%20loans%20that%20don't%20have%20an%20early%20payoff%20penalty.%20Then%2C%20we%20pay%20off%20the%20loans%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20not%20had%20a%20car%20payment%20in%20five%20years.%20Would%20I%20like%20to%20drive%20a%20nicer%20car%3F%20Sometimes.%20However%2C%20I%20realize%20that%20driving%20a%20new%20car%20does%20not%20help%20me%20meet%20my%20goals%20of%20being%20debt-free%20and%20retiring%20early.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20plunging%20an%20extra%20%241%2C100%20a%20month%20from%20two%20would-be%20car%20payments%20into%20our%20mortgage%20principal%20does%20help%20us%20meet%20our%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3ECheck%20today's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%3E%20average%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20amount%20of%20house%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20financial%20windfalls%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20savings%20strategy%20we%20learned%20from%20my%20mother-in-law%20is%20to%20always%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20financial%20windfalls.%20A%20windfall%20could%20be%20a%20tax%20return%2C%20bonus%2C%20gift%2C%20or%20additional%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20had%20young%20children%2C%20my%20mother-in-law%20strategically%20saved%20her%20annual%20tax%20return%20to%20pay%20for%20summer%20childcare.%20Other%20times%2C%20she%20used%20it%20to%20pay%20for%20home%20improvements.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20few%20years%2C%20she%20bought%20new%20windows%20for%20her%20home%20a%20few%20at%20a%20time.%20She%20didn't%20put%20these%20expenses%20on%20a%20credit%20card%20or%20spend%20her%20tax%20return%20frivolously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20we%20bought%20our%20home%2C%20my%20mother-in-law%20also%20encouraged%20us%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20make%20extra%20house%20payments.%20We%20started%20by%20simply%20paying%20an%20extra%20%24150%20on%20our%20principal%20every%20month.%20She%20also%20explained%20that%20people%20who%20get%20paid%20every%20two%20weeks%20will%20get%20an%20%26quot%3Bextra%26quot%3B%20paycheck%20twice%20a%20year%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20many%20Fridays%20occur%20in%20the%20month.%20If%20you%20account%20for%20your%20monthly%20expenses%20based%20on%20two%20paydays%20a%20month%2C%20this%20%26quot%3Bextra%26quot%3B%20paycheck%20can%20be%20treated%20like%20a%20windfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20take%20her%20advice%20right%20away%2C%20but%20eventually%2C%20we%20applied%20our%20%26quot%3Bextra%26quot%3B%20paychecks%20and%20other%20bonuses%20to%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20chipping%20away%20at%20the%20principal%20a%20few%20hundred%20or%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEliminating%20childcare%20expenses%20was%20a%20major%20windfall%20for%20us.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20this%20cost%20was%20nearly%20equivalent%20to%20our%20house%20payment.%20When%20my%20husband's%20job%20changed%20in%202017%20and%20our%20children%20grew%20out%20of%20needing%20before-%20and%20after-school%20care%2C%20we%20snowballed%20the%20extra%20money%20into%20our%20mortgage%20payment%2C%20helping%20to%20bring%20it%20down%20to%20zero%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20our%20mortgage%20gone%20and%20our%20sights%20on%20other%20financial%20goals%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20grateful%20for%20our%20parents%20and%20the%20lessons%20they%20taught%20us%20about%20living%20within%20our%20means.%20It%20led%20us%20to%20paying%20off%20our%20mortgage%20early%2C%20which%20has%20allowed%20us%20both%20to%20choose%20more%20fulfilling%20work%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20our%20daughters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20January%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaid-off-mortgage-more-than-decade-early-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716414601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ff491393793140019e28642%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaid-off-mortgage-more-than-decade-early-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20living%20below%20their%20means%2C%20the%20couple%20was%20able%20to%20get%20out%20of%20mortgage%20debt%20by%20ages%2039%20and%2037%20%E2%80%94%20all%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20pandemic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%2